{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the promise of AI, its deployment in healthcare also carries significant risks.",
    "These include concerns about data privacy, algorithmic bias, transparency, and potential unintended hallucinations with impact on patient safety 2.",
    "To ensure that AI is used responsibly and ethically, it is imperative to establish robust governance frameworks that mitigate these risks across the AI supply chain.",
    "Such AI governance frameworks can become the springboard for safe and effective innovation in healthcare settings.",
    "The adoption of AI governance in healthcare is increasingly being shaped by federal agencies that have introduced guidelines to promote safety, effectiveness, and transparency."
  ]
}